+ Class Methods

++ Public

* Solar::apiVersion() -- Returns the API version for Solar.

* Solar::config() -- Safely gets a configuration group array or element value.

* Solar::cookie() -- Safely gets the value of an element from the $_COOKIE array.

* Solar::dependency() -- Returns a dependency object.

* Solar::dump() -- Dumps a variable to output.

* Solar::exception() -- Generates a simple exception, but does not throw it.

* Solar::factory() -- Convenience method to instantiate and configure an object.

* Solar::fileExists() -- Hack for [[php file_exists()]] that checks the include_path.

* Solar::files() -- Safely gets the value of an element from the $_FILES array.

* Solar::fixdir() -- "Fixes" a directory string for the operating system.

* Solar::get() -- Safely gets the value of an element from the $_GET array.

* Solar::getLocale() -- Returns the current locale code.

* Solar::isRegistered() -- Check to see if an object name already exists in the registry.

* Solar::loadClass() -- Loads a class file from the include_path.

* Solar::locale() -- Gets the translated locale string for a class and key.

* Solar::pathinfo() -- Safely gets the value of $_SERVER['PATH_INFO'] element.

* Solar::post() -- Safely gets the value of an element from the $_POST array.

* Solar::register() -- Registers an object under a unique name.

* Solar::registry() -- Accesses an object in the registry.

* Solar::run() -- Uses [[php include()]] to run a script in a limited scope.

* Solar::server() -- Safely gets the value of an element from the $_SERVER array.

* Solar::session() -- Safely gets the value of an element from the $_SESSION array.

* Solar::setLocale() -- Sets the locale code and clears out previous locale strings.

* Solar::start() -- Starts Solar: loads configuration values and and sets up the environment.

* Solar::stop() -- Stops Solar: run stop scripts.

++ Protected

* Solar::_dispelQuotes() -- A stripslashes() alias that supports array_walk_recursive().

* Solar::_dispelSybase() -- A str_replace() for Sybase quotes; supports array_walk_recursive().

* Solar::_globalsQuotes() -- Performs some security on globals, removes magic quotes if turned on.

* Solar::_super() -- Fetches a superglobal value by key, or a default value.

++ Private

* Solar::__construct() -- Constructor is disabled to enforce a singleton pattern.